00:17:57,150 --> 00:17:58,519
You were a prosecutor, Director Lee.

269
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:01,349
What? I mean,

270
00:18:01,849 --> 00:18:04,420
this isn't about punishment.

271
00:18:05,119 --> 00:18:07,559
The company's image is at stake.

272
00:18:07,829 --> 00:18:11,329
If you want it to go away quietly,
you should resign for now.

273
00:18:11,329 --> 00:18:12,430
"Resign"?

274
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:17,130
You guys have done a great job
covering up your own mistakes.

275
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,869
And now you're
telling me to resign...

276
00:18:19,869 --> 00:18:21,339
under the pretext
of the company's dignity?

277
00:18:21,769 --> 00:18:22,839
Then what?

278
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:24,539
Do you want to hold a
stockholders' meeting?

279
00:18:25,039 --> 00:18:26,680
What are you guys doing?

280
00:18:27,410 --> 00:18:29,849
You guys got him to resign
with some tricks three years ago.

281
00:18:29,849 --> 00:18:31,250
Do you think it will work again?

282
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:34,019
It'd be better to keep this quiet.

283
00:18:34,019 --> 00:18:35,119
Are the rest of you...

284
00:18:36,049 --> 00:18:38,119
with Director Park?

285
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:51,470
Are you...

286
00:18:53,339 --> 00:18:54,509
with him?

287
00:19:03,779 --> 00:19:04,880
I can't see...

288
00:19:06,279 --> 00:19:09,690
who and how many of them
are on my side.

289
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:12,390
I can't see anything.

290
00:19:17,859 --> 00:19:19,599
What? Why is it taking so long?

291
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:21,799
Let's take a show of hands then.

292
00:19:24,130 --> 00:19:25,240
"A show of hands"?

293
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,710
Then we can decide immediately.

294
00:19:30,869 --> 00:19:31,880
Gosh.

295
00:19:32,740 --> 00:19:36,380
Do you really have to do this?

296
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:38,349
My goodness.

297
00:19:39,019 --> 00:19:41,519
It's not like this is an election
for class presidents.

298
00:19:41,950 --> 00:19:44,819
6. I need at least
6 people on my side.

299
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:47,119
Mom will take my side anyway.

300
00:19:47,289 --> 00:19:49,059
Those two are always on my side.

301
00:19:49,460 --> 00:19:52,660
Director Lee. I thought
I could win him over.

302
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:55,529
Either he or Director Kim
would raise his hand.

303
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,940
And Dae Ju is definitely on my side.
So I've got five.

304
00:19:59,940 --> 00:20:01,509
Which means it can be six.

305
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:05,279
If you don't like it,
just go ahead and resign.

306
00:20:05,279 --> 00:20:06,509
I'll take a show of hands.

307
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:08,109
Min Ik.

308
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:11,819
Chairman. Let's continue.

309
00:20:12,279 --> 00:20:15,990
Okay. I guess
we have no other choice.

310
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:17,519
Let's continue then.

311
00:20:18,589 --> 00:20:22,329
If 6 out of 11 directors here
raise their hands,

312
00:20:22,829 --> 00:20:24,190
it will be passed.

313
00:20:26,329 --> 00:20:28,630
Director Woo, you go first.

314
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:54,960
Director Lee.

315
00:21:10,609 --> 00:21:11,809
They're five.

316
00:21:12,339 --> 00:21:14,210
So it's rejected, right?

317
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:15,250
Wait.

318
00:21:16,210 --> 00:21:17,410
We have one person left.

319
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:24,150
Are you for...

320
00:21:25,319 --> 00:21:26,390
or against it?

321
00:21:33,529 --> 00:21:34,900
Director Gi Dae Ju.

322
00:21:44,140 --> 00:21:45,180
I'm for it.

323
00:21:58,490 --> 00:22:00,460
Secretary Jeong, will you
give us a minute?

324
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:03,789
Yes, Director Gi.

325
00:22:23,779 --> 00:22:25,519
What is going on?

326
00:22:25,950 --> 00:22:27,880
Even a story
with a lot of reversal...

327
00:22:29,420 --> 00:22:31,319
should have some probability.

328
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:33,819
You said you'd quit two days ago.

329
00:22:34,930 --> 00:22:36,759
But you kicked me
out of the board today?

330
00:22:36,759 --> 00:22:37,759
Let's take this
to the stockholders' meeting.

331
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:39,660
What?

332
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:41,670
If you don't resign voluntarily,

333
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,869
they'd do anything
to drag you down...

334
00:22:44,869 --> 00:22:47,369
until a new president is elected.
Don't you get it?

335
00:22:52,309 --> 00:22:53,680
What if it doesn't work
at the stockholders' meeting?

336
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:54,680
Why wouldn't it?

337
00:22:55,410 --> 00:22:56,980
It's not like you're ill.

338
00:22:59,019 --> 00:23:01,150
They could do it three years ago
because you were sick,

339
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:02,349
but you're just fine now.

340
00:23:03,150 --> 00:23:06,089
One third of stockholders
must attend the meeting.

341
00:23:06,490 --> 00:23:08,059
It's highly likely that
the meeting will be cancelled.

342
00:23:08,559 --> 00:23:10,490
We have only two months
left before the election.

343
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:12,759
If it is cancelled, we can't
call another meeting in time.

344
00:23:13,529 --> 00:23:15,400
Even if a stockholders' meeting
takes place,

345
00:23:15,730 --> 00:23:19,039
it might get rejected. Then the
board won't be able to do anything.

346
00:23:23,539 --> 00:23:27,079
If you cared for me that much,
let me ask you something.

347
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:33,119
Why did you say you'd quit?

348
00:23:39,019 --> 00:23:40,019
Why?

349
00:23:57,039 --> 00:23:58,039
Well...

350
00:24:00,009 --> 00:24:02,680
I went to the police
station yesterday.

351
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:06,720
You went there after all.

352
00:24:08,650 --> 00:24:10,420
What did you tell them?

353
00:24:11,019 --> 00:24:12,890
I told them the truth.

354
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:14,589
Yes, Director Gi.

355
00:24:15,559 --> 00:24:19,200
- I'll be a little late tomorrow.
- Hwangcheon intersection.

356
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:21,200
Turn left at the intersection.

357
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:24,230
Something urgent came up,
so I went to my mom's that night.

358
00:24:29,839 --> 00:24:33,440
And I didn't see you that night.

359
00:24:37,980 --> 00:24:39,279
I heard it, Boss.

360
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:43,089
I'm sorry. I'll look into it again.

361
00:24:46,519 --> 00:24:48,259
So they took a show of hands.

362
00:24:48,829 --> 00:24:50,759
And six of them raised their hands.

363
00:24:51,660 --> 00:24:52,799
So what's happening?

364
00:24:52,799 --> 00:24:54,200
It's obvious.

365
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,869
If he gets dismissed
at the stockholders' meeting,

366
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,099
there's no way...

367
00:24:57,569 --> 00:24:58,900
he'll be the president.

368
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:02,609
Most of them resign voluntarily
before it happens, though.

369
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:05,640
Ms. Lee.

370
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,849
- Hello.
- Hello.

371
00:25:10,210 --> 00:25:12,220
Ms. Lee, I'm sorry.

372
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:14,619
But I should get going now.
Please excuse me.

373
00:25:20,059 --> 00:25:21,660
Where is she running to
so hurriedly?

374
00:25:22,089 --> 00:25:23,329
Did you not hear it?

375
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:25,529
The video of Director Do
assaulting his driver...

376
00:25:25,529 --> 00:25:26,599
is going around.

377
00:25:28,430 --> 00:25:31,740
There's a video?

378
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,170
- Fire him immediately.
- Mom.

379
00:25:35,339 --> 00:25:38,539
You saw Dae Ju raise his hand
at the meeting.

380
00:25:40,210 --> 00:25:42,380
You've always recklessly
believed in people too much.

381
00:25:42,849 --> 00:25:45,750
How can you still trust people
after what happened three years ago?

382
00:25:48,289 --> 00:25:49,549
(3 years ago)

383
00:25:49,549 --> 00:25:50,990
Gloripen capsule.

384
00:25:51,759 --> 00:25:54,390
How did you get my prescription?

385
00:25:54,990 --> 00:25:57,829
Do you know
what this medicine is for?

386
00:25:58,359 --> 00:26:00,799
It's to treat degenerative
psychogenic syndromes...

387
00:26:00,799 --> 00:26:02,470
due to a cerebral vascular defect.

388
00:26:02,730 --> 00:26:05,400
This equals to having
dementia or brain disease...

389
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:07,269
as side effects later on.

390
00:26:07,970 --> 00:26:10,039
His mind still comes and goes?

391
00:26:10,039 --> 00:26:11,170
I thought he was fully recovered.

392
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:13,009
A person with dementia
can't run this company.

393
00:26:13,009 --> 00:26:15,650
What's going on?
He has a problem with his brain?

394
00:26:16,009 --> 00:26:18,380
I said you're fine.
Why do you keep coming to me?

395
00:26:18,650 --> 00:26:22,619
I need you to check thoroughly
to see if I'm really fine.

396
00:26:23,019 --> 00:26:25,589
I told you. The president election
is just around the corner.

397
00:26:25,759 --> 00:26:27,220
If you're so worried,

398
00:26:27,220 --> 00:26:29,430
why don't you try this?

399
00:26:29,529 --> 00:26:30,589
What is it?

400
00:26:31,059 --> 00:26:33,730
It's a kind of brain enhancer. It's
basically a nutritional supplement.

401
00:26:33,730 --> 00:26:36,430
This is exactly what anxious
students ask when they have exams.

402
00:26:38,799 --> 00:26:39,839
I knew you were going to give
something to me.

403
00:26:43,910 --> 00:26:45,140
(Prescription)

404
00:26:47,309 --> 00:26:48,750
Secretary Lee...

405
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:49,750
(President Sim Hae Yong)

406
00:26:50,309 --> 00:26:52,880
It's been over 10 years since
I've officially fully recovered.

407
00:26:53,549 --> 00:26:55,819
My doctor prescribed the medicine
for just in case.

408
00:26:55,819 --> 00:26:57,490
"One who is physically
or mentally challenged..."

409
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:59,890
"and therefore prevented
from doing one's duty..."

410
00:27:00,089 --> 00:27:02,059
"can't be elected as president."

411
00:27:02,259 --> 00:27:05,660
You know this is written on our
articles of incorporation, right?

412
00:27:08,259 --> 00:27:10,369
How could you not know...
your own secretary...

413
00:27:10,369 --> 00:27:11,970
was with them? You idiot.

414
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,869
You even tried to promote her
to a permanent employee.

415
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:17,069
People would do anything for
some stash of money.

416
00:27:24,450 --> 00:27:25,549
It's more like,

417
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:29,619
those who have money
manipulate other people with money.

418
00:27:32,319 --> 00:27:34,819
Ma'am, you don't have to prepare
my dinner.

419
00:27:38,130 --> 00:27:39,730
I haven't eaten,

420
00:27:40,329 --> 00:27:41,599
but I'm full, again.

421
00:27:45,369 --> 00:27:49,710
I'm going to this mountain
cuckoo, cuckoo

422
00:27:50,170 --> 00:27:51,470
I'm going to this mountain

423
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:53,539
Resign before
the stockholders' meeting.

424
00:27:53,910 --> 00:27:55,250
I'll think about it.

425
00:27:56,079 --> 00:27:57,380
Just resign.

426
00:27:57,579 --> 00:28:00,380
Before you humiliate yourself
with the critical video evidence.

427
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:02,950
Including Gi Dae Ju, your driver,
and your secretary,

428
00:28:03,089 --> 00:28:05,059
dismiss everyone near you.

429
00:28:42,059 --> 00:28:44,059
Since when you, as a secretary,

430
00:28:44,059 --> 00:28:47,000
were allowed to come to
your boss' place and call him out?

431
00:28:48,470 --> 00:28:50,670
Are you going to resign?

432
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:55,509
Don't resign.

433
00:28:57,369 --> 00:28:58,809
Are orders...

434
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:02,880
supposed to be given
from secretaries to their bosses?

435
00:29:03,609 --> 00:29:06,480
Shouldn't it be
the other way around?

436
00:29:08,220 --> 00:29:09,789
Let's switch our positions
just for today.

437
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:12,690
I need to give an order to you.

438
00:29:13,490 --> 00:29:15,430
Please don't resign, sir.

439
00:29:15,789 --> 00:29:17,289
If I resign from the board,

440
00:29:17,890 --> 00:29:20,529
of course I can't be the president,

441
00:29:20,529 --> 00:29:22,829
but it doesn't mean
I can't keep my current position.

442
00:29:22,829 --> 00:29:25,539
Therefore, your contract will stay.

443
00:29:26,569 --> 00:29:28,670
Do you think I'm doing this
for the contract?

444
00:29:28,670 --> 00:29:29,710
You're not?

445
00:29:35,109 --> 00:29:36,579
I found it cool.

446
00:29:39,650 --> 00:29:42,490
When you dared to swallow
your pride, came to me,

447
00:29:43,819 --> 00:29:45,690
and asked me to come back.

448
00:29:47,619 --> 00:29:50,630
When you said you wouldn't be
defeated by your disease,

449
00:29:51,859 --> 00:29:53,630
even if there's no cure for it.

450
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:59,339
When you memorized all employees'
heights and hairstyles...

451
00:30:00,140 --> 00:30:03,009
and then welcomed
the directors without any problem.

452
00:30:10,380 --> 00:30:12,680
What are you doing?
You're flattering me.

453
00:30:14,079 --> 00:30:17,220
When my boss gets flattered,
I get flattered.

454
00:30:18,190 --> 00:30:19,759
When my boss gets depressed,

455
00:30:20,460 --> 00:30:23,430
I get down too.
That happens to be my job.

456
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:27,160
Don't give up.

457
00:30:27,900 --> 00:30:29,900
Keep running
until you can be the president.

458
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,170
I'll help you.

459
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:36,869
By making my boss cool,

460
00:30:38,039 --> 00:30:40,140
I can make myself cool too.

461
00:30:47,049 --> 00:30:48,349
Let's wait for him.

462
00:30:48,349 --> 00:30:50,019
It won't be easy for him
to bring it up.

463
00:30:50,019 --> 00:30:53,220
I'm so hungry. I'm starving.

464
00:30:53,519 --> 00:30:54,589
- Darn it.
- Good grief.

465
00:31:17,779 --> 00:31:18,819
About resignation...

466
00:31:20,019 --> 00:31:22,150
Good. You should just say it now.

467
00:31:22,150 --> 00:31:23,720
You made the right decision.

468
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:26,160
Let's wrap it up now.

469
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:29,430
How about seolleongtang for brunch?

470
00:31:29,430 --> 00:31:30,460
I'm not resigning.

471
00:31:30,829 --> 00:31:31,890
What?

472
00:31:33,299 --> 00:31:35,769
Do Min Ik, why...

473
00:31:36,599 --> 00:31:39,200
My uncle has always been
my role model.

474
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,000
Just like three years ago,

475
00:31:41,740 --> 00:31:44,839
he never gives up. He has
always been doing his utmost.

476
00:31:45,579 --> 00:31:48,710
And as a young man, I shouldn't be
discouraged by such a minor issue.

477
00:31:49,210 --> 00:31:51,680
Besides, now I have someone
who will help me...

478
00:31:52,019 --> 00:31:53,519
become the president.

479
00:31:55,019 --> 00:31:58,119
From now on, I'm going to
just bite the bullet and go for it.

480
00:31:58,690 --> 00:32:00,390
Let's see who will cross...

481
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:02,490
the finish line first.

482
00:32:21,539 --> 00:32:22,650
I just did it.

483
00:32:22,910 --> 00:32:24,180
Well done.

484
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:27,119
Now, what should we do first?

485
00:32:27,980 --> 00:32:29,589
We should change your office first.

486
00:32:30,390 --> 00:32:33,390
We never know. Someone might be
monitoring us again.

487
00:32:35,859 --> 00:32:37,329
Jung Hee, I'm home.

488
00:32:38,660 --> 00:32:40,660
How come you're home
in the middle of the day, ma'am?

489
00:32:43,299 --> 00:32:44,369
What's that?

490
00:32:44,599 --> 00:32:45,869
This is mine, right?

491
00:32:46,069 --> 00:32:48,599
The sleeves are a bit too long.

492
00:32:52,039 --> 00:32:53,539
Wait, did you get hurt?

493
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:04,789
Is it from this bag?

494
00:33:08,289 --> 00:33:11,130
It's my boss' suit!

495
00:33:11,759 --> 00:33:14,630
No wonder it felt nice.

496
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,430
Take if off already!

497
00:33:17,730 --> 00:33:19,670
You have no idea what this is.

498
00:33:22,039 --> 00:33:25,440
The shirt. Didn't you smell
blood from the shirt?

499
00:33:27,980 --> 00:33:30,950
I should have taken this
to the laundry shop.

500
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,079
Why did I forget that?

501
00:33:35,349 --> 00:33:36,390
What was the sound?

502
00:33:42,759 --> 00:33:44,130
Maybe it's Director Do's.

503
00:33:44,230 --> 00:33:45,500
Kyun Woo!

504
00:33:45,829 --> 00:33:48,460
I guess I'm a woman after all.

505
00:33:50,099 --> 00:33:51,430
Kyun Woo!

506
00:33:52,700 --> 00:33:54,039
I'm sorry!

507
00:33:57,769 --> 00:34:01,210
(Movie audition for
"My Sassy Court Maid")

508
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:09,289
Ma'am.

509
00:34:13,489 --> 00:34:15,590
Your mother says
you look pretty, right?

510
00:34:16,489 --> 00:34:18,230
I'm sure she says Jun Ji Hyun is
not as pretty as you.

511
00:34:18,530 --> 00:34:20,800
And that you could be
a more successful actress than her.

512
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:23,300
If you think I was bad, just say it.

513
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:25,639
Don't get my mother involved.
It's unfair.

514
00:34:25,639 --> 00:34:27,940
Okay. You are bad. Next!

515
00:34:28,639 --> 00:34:30,409
- Is that it?
- Of course that's it.

516
00:34:31,010 --> 00:34:33,809
You're not only horrible at acting,
but also lashed at me.

517
00:34:34,380 --> 00:34:35,380
What did you expect?

518
00:34:35,380 --> 00:34:38,050
You made a personal attack
against me first, old lady.

519
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:39,849
"Old lady"?

520
00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:41,050
Please don't...

521
00:34:41,980 --> 00:34:43,619
Ma'am! Please calm down!

522
00:34:44,650 --> 00:34:47,320
And you just made a personal attack
against me!

523
00:34:47,559 --> 00:34:51,030
One can only be
either a person or a woman.

524
00:34:51,389 --> 00:34:53,130
How dare you discriminate me
by calling me an old lady?

525
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:54,929
I'm the one who got discriminated.

526
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:56,929
You're a judge,
but you didn't look at me.

527
00:34:56,929 --> 00:34:58,130
You were only looking at your phone.

528
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:00,800
